<!-- Start Body -->
I have been using Adderall for almost two years now. I am not prescribed to it nor have I ever been. I have a few friends of mine though that are, but do not take it so they sell it or give it away. <BR>
<BR>
At this point I'm very much addicted to it and I cannot leave it alone. I love it so much. I love the way it opens me up. I am a very shy person but with Adderall I can talk to anyone so I think. I hate the come downs though. It's okay if I only take one but sometimes we'll just keep taking them for days at a time and not sleep whatsoever. We all call this 'adderollin' I guess it's pretty pathetic. My family knows I used to take it but they think I got off of it. I did quit though for a few months but as soon as I found it again, it all started over. I want to get off of it. I crave it every day. If I go for more than a couple days without it I feel as if I might go crazy. I know it's harmful for my health, but I feel so euphoric when I'm on it. I wish it didn't exist.<!-- End Body -->
<br/><br style="clear:both;"/>


